<title>INDIA: India Infosys shr soars on Q1 results.</title>
<headline>India Infosys shr soars on Q1 results.</headline>
<dateline>BOMBAY 1997-07-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares of Indian software firm Infosys Technologies Ltd soared after the company said its first quarter profits doubled, brokers said.</p>
<p>The share leapt 145 rupees, or 7.23 percent, to 2,149 after the firm said its net profit for the first three months to June 30, 1997 rose to 92.2 million rupees from 45.5 million rupees.  </p>
<p>The company said its net profit jumped 103 percent on 73 percent increase in total revenues.</p>
<p>Total income grew to 458.1 million rupees in the first quarter from 264.3 million in the same period a year ago, of which overseas income totalled 437.9 million rupees against 234.8 million.</p>
<p>--Bombay equities desk +91-22-265-9000</p>
